history.content: I took Math 54 in Spring 2020. This fall, I'm planning on taking CS70 to apply to declare for L&S CS. I'm trying to decide between enrolling in EECS16A, EECS47D, or neither, given that I'm planning on taking 16B in spring 2021. There's not a whole lot of info on EECS47D but I'm leaning in that direction since I already took math 54 and it sounds like part of 16A is linear algebra anyway. Has anyone taken 47D and if so, what was your experience?
